To convert a thumbdrive from FAT32 to NTFS on Windows XP:

Insert the drive into the USB slot.  It should automount.
Right click on the drive's icon in My Computer:
	Properties->Hardware->Properties->Policies
	Make sure write caching is not enabled, and that
	Optimize for Performance is selected

At command prompt, assuming removable drive is drive F: in this example:

convert f: /fs:ntfs
